.TH CYGNUS-PAINT 0.3-2 "March 2026" "Version 0.3-2" "Cygnus Paint App"
.SH NAME
cygnus-paint \- A simple paint application for Cygnus WM.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cygnus-paint

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cygnus-paint
is a lightweight painting application built with SFML. It allows users to draw freehand, fill areas with color, undo/redo actions, and zoom in/out on the canvas.

.SH CONTROLS
The application is controlled primarily via the mouse.

.TP
.B Left Click (Canvas)
Draw with the current brush or fill an area with the bucket tool.
.TP
.B Left Click (Toolbar)
Select tools, colors, adjust brush size, undo/redo actions, zoom, and save.

.SH TOOLBAR BUTTONS
.TP
.B Brush
Selects the freehand drawing tool.
.TP
.B Bucket
Selects the flood fill tool.
.TP
.B - / +
Decrease or increase the brush size (1-50 pixels).
.TP
.B Undo / Redo
Step backward or forward through the drawing history (up to 20 steps).
.TP
.B Z In / Z Out
Zoom in or out of the canvas.
.TP
.B Save
Saves the current canvas to \fB~/Pictures/drawing.png\fR. If the HOME environment variable is not set, saves to \fBrawing.png\fR in the current directory.

.SH COLORS
The palette includes a selection of basic colors:
Black, White, Gray, Red, Orange, Yellow, Blue, Green, Pink, Purple, and Brown (light/dark variants).

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/Pictures/drawing.png
Default save location for drawings.

